# Requiem Nexus — Cursor AI Rules

This is a .NET 10 / C# 14 / Blazor Server modular monolith for Vampire: The Requiem 2e character
management. It is also an intentional learning artifact — the **Grimoire**. Every architectural
decision is teachable. When suggesting code, explain *why* the pattern exists, not just *what* it does.

## Primary Reference Files
- `agents.md` — agent startup checklist, architectural laws, forbidden patterns, security rules
- `docs/Architecture.md` — layer diagram, request flow, performance budgets
- `docs/mission.md` — current phase (Phase 6 active), completed phases, non-goals

## Stack
.NET 10 · C# 14 · Blazor Server · EF Core (SQLite dev / PostgreSQL prod) · Redis · SignalR ·
.NET Aspire · AWS CDK (.NET) · StyleCop.Analyzers · Serilog + OpenTelemetry

---

## Layer Dependency Law (Sacred — Never Violate)

```
Web → Application → Domain ← Data (Infrastructure)
```

- `Domain` has ZERO dependencies on `Data` or `Web`
- `Data` serves Domain — never drives it
- `Web` holds no business rules and makes no authorization decisions
- Never inject `ApplicationDbContext` into a Web component or Razor page directly

---

## The Rule of One (Non-Negotiable)

- One type per file — every class, interface, record, and enum has its own `.cs` file
- File name must exactly match the type name
- Never add a second type to an existing file — create a new file
- Violations cause CI pipeline failure (`/warnaserror`)

---

## C# 14 Style (Use These Patterns)

```csharp
// PRIMARY CONSTRUCTORS — always prefer over field injection boilerplate
public class CampaignService(ApplicationDbContext dbContext, ILogger<CampaignService> logger)
    : ICampaignService
{
    private readonly ApplicationDbContext _dbContext = dbContext;
    private readonly ILogger<CampaignService> _logger = logger;
}

// COLLECTION EXPRESSIONS — use [] syntax over new List<T>()
List<int> ids = [1, 2, 3];
string[] names = ["Alice", "Bob"];

// PRIVATE FIELDS — underscore + camelCase (StyleCop enforced)
private readonly ILogger<T> _logger;
private int _count;

// XML DOC COMMENTS — required on all public members in Domain and Application
/// <summary>Returns the archived characters owned by the given user.</summary>
public async Task<List<Character>> GetArchivedCharactersAsync(string userId)
```

---

## Error Handling Law

- Domain methods return `Result<T>` — NEVER throw for expected business failures
- Application layer translates `Result.Failure` → HTTP status codes or UI messages
- Infrastructure catches external failures, wraps them in domain-friendly types
- Every `catch` must log or rethrow — silent swallowing is a defect

---

## The Masquerade — Security Protocol (All 4 Steps Required)

Every data-mutating operation must follow this exact sequence:

```csharp
// Step 1 — Extract authenticated user ID from security context
var userId = _httpContextAccessor.HttpContext!.User.FindFirstValue(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)!;

// Step 2 — Load the target entity
var entity = await _dbContext.Things.FindAsync(id)
    ?? throw new InvalidOperationException($"Entity {id} not found.");

// Step 3 — VERIFY OWNERSHIP (never skip — this is the security guarantee)
if (entity.OwnerId != userId)
    throw new UnauthorizedAccessException("Access denied.");

// Step 4 — Proceed
entity.DoMutation();
await _dbContext.SaveChangesAsync();
```

Skipping Step 3 is a security defect. Use `AuthorizationHelper.RequireCharacterAccessAsync()` or
`RequireStorytellerAsync()` for the standard patterns already in the codebase.
(Canonical implementation: `src/RequiemNexus.Application/Services/AuthorizationHelper.cs`)

---

## Forbidden Patterns

- No shared `Common` or `Utils` projects — shared logic belongs in Domain
- No cross-domain object references — use explicit contracts
- No `SELECT *` equivalents — always project only needed columns
- No N+1 queries — use `.Include()` or explicit projections
- No `#if DEBUG` — environment behavior is driven by configuration
- No direct database access from Domain layer
- No business logic in Web layer

---

## EF Core Patterns

```csharp
// Always use AsNoTracking() for read-only queries
var result = await _dbContext.Characters
    .Include(c => c.Clan)
    .Where(c => c.ApplicationUserId == userId && !c.IsArchived)
    .AsNoTracking()
    .ToListAsync();

// Project to DTOs — never return raw EF entities from Application layer
// when only partial data is needed
```

---

## Observability (Required for New Operations)

Every significant operation must emit a structured Serilog log entry:

```csharp
// CORRECT — structured parameters
_logger.LogInformation("Character {CharacterId} archived by user {UserId}", id, userId);

// WRONG — string interpolation loses structure
_logger.LogInformation($"Character {id} archived by {userId}");
```

---

## Testing Requirements

| New Code | Required Test |
|----------|---------------|
| Domain logic | Unit test in `RequiemNexus.Domain.Tests` |
| Application service | Integration test in `RequiemNexus.Data.Tests` |
| Authorization flow | Integration test in `RequiemNexus.Data.Tests` |

---

## StyleCop Compliance

- `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` runs in CI — code must pass
- XML doc comments required on all `public` members in Domain and Application
- Run `dotnet format` before every commit
- System usings sorted first, then alphabetical within groups

---

## Domain Glossary (Use These Terms)

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Chronicle | A campaign or ongoing story (`Campaign` entity) |
| Clan | A vampire bloodline (`Clan` entity) |
| Discipline | A supernatural power (`Discipline` / `DisciplinePower` entities) |
| Merit | A character advantage (`Merit` entity) |
| Beats | XP increments (`Beats` on `Character`) |
| Covenant | Political faction — a character attribute, not an entity |
| Touchstone | Mortal anchor to humanity — a character field |

---

## Grimoire Learning Mode

When suggesting code or explaining a decision, connect it to the architectural principle it
demonstrates. Examples:

- "This uses a primary constructor (C# 14) rather than the old `[Inject]` pattern to make
  dependencies explicit at construction time — that's the Antigravity principle 'Traceability
  beats cleverness.'"
- "We return `Result<T>` here instead of throwing because Domain methods must never throw for
  expected failures — the Application layer decides what HTTP status code that maps to."
- "This query uses `AsNoTracking()` because we're only reading for display — tracking adds
  EF Core overhead with no benefit when we don't intend to update the entity."

